response.Q0: I decided to find the best route by inspecting all nodes but keeping the final node's amount in mind (I didn't mind spending too much on nodes if the last node could at least be positive), however, I always tried to aim for a final node above 70 (preferably above 80, but if it cost me less and gave me a favourable final node, I chose it).
response.Q1: I realized that I didn't need to follow a set path/route when inspecting the nodes, so I simply checked the final nodes for the amount I desired and then followed any path leading to it because I knew that even if the majority of the route would be negative, the positive points in the final node would result in my score being positive.
response.Q2: I think with every new game the beginning is a little challenging while you get your feet wet, but overall, I don't think it was a difficult game and so my performance was solely based on figuring out that I didn't need to follow a set path when inspecting the nodes. When I realized that, my performance was better because I managed to reduce the amount I spent inspecting the nodes. The other thing was simply balancing inspecting nodes within the timeframe while remembering where I saw the positive/desired final nodes (the highest number).
